        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(codex): index rollout transcript ids",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nCodex native-subagent reconciliation scans every transcript file against every missing child thread id. With many pending children, that turns one filesystem walk into a files-by-children comparison loop.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nCodex recorder transcripts use the canonical `rollout-<timestamp>-<thread-id>.jsonl` filename. The monitor now extracts that thread id and performs a set lookup, while keeping the existing substring fallback for non-canonical files.\n\n## User Impact\n\nLarge Codex session trees reconcile pending native subagents with less CPU work and the same transcript completion behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Focused tests: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-subagent-monitor.test.ts`\n- Result: 33 tests passed.\n- Fresh autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Codex recorder contract checked in `codex-rs/rollout/src/recorder_tests.rs`.\n- Rebased source commit: `e314154269`\n",
